          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "EDEG",
                "MOSEP",
                "BCINT",
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "A Highly Defocussed, Diffused and Collimated Beam was",
                "Used. The Typical Irradiation Condition was",
                "1 Microampere For 300 Sec. Energy Degradation was",
                "Calculated According to C.F.Williamson Et Al.,",
                "Cea-3042(1966)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Counting Error at the 95.5% Confidence",
                "Level was Less Than 3%. The Greatest Errors Arise from",
                "The Uncertainties in the Irradiation Parameters",
                "Resulting from any Lack of Uniformity in the Germanium",
                "Thickness (< 2%), and Specifically from Heterogeneous",
                "Distribution, If any.",
                "Impurities Present in the Target Other Than Ge were",
                "Smaller Than 1%.",
                "Recoil Losses from the Polystyrene Matrix were Very",
                "Small and were Neglected in Computing the Cross",
                "Sections. Overall Errors are Typically of the Order of",
                "14%.  The Uncertainty in the Incident Particle Beam",
                "Energy was Estimated As 1%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Production of Se-73 For Radiotracer Studies was",
                "Investigated with He-3 and He-4 Activation. An Optimum",
                "Thick Target Production Rate of 933 Micro-Ci/Micro-Ahr",
                " (RADIONUCLIDIC PURITY > 99.99%) Was Found Using the",
                "Ge-72(HE-3,2N)Se-73 Reaction on Isotopically Enriched",
                "Ge-72 with He-3 Degraded from 37 MeV to 18 MeV on a 151",
                "Mg/Cm**2 Target of Ge-Dioxide.  Thin Target Production",
                "Yields of Radionuclidic Impurities (AS-71,72,74,76 AND",
                "SE-75) Produced by He-3 and He-4 Reactions were Given",
                "In Figures."
              ]
            }
          ],
